2026-03-28T19:15:42.047Z JOY-0089 comment.added "When joy ai reset removes an AI tool configuration, it should also:\n1. Remove the AI member's public_key from project.yaml (invalidates all delegation tokens signed for that member)\n2. Remove the AI member's session file if one exists\n3. Optionally remove the AI member from project.yaml entirely\n\nWithout this, stale tokens and sessions could persist after a tool is deconfigured. The token invalidation happens implicitly via public_key removal -- validate_token checks the delegating human's key, but the AI member check in auth_with_token verifies the AI is still registered." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
