2026-03-28T20:47:53.029Z JOY-008A comment.added "Session files are stored per project ID (sessions/JOY.json), not per member. When a second member authenticates (e.g. AI via token), their session overwrites the first member's session file. This means only one member can have an active session at a time per project.\n\nFix: include member ID in session filename, e.g. sessions/JOY--horst.schwarz@joydev.com.json\n\nIntegration test needed: two members authenticate, verify both sessions exist independently." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T20:48:06.664Z JOY-008B comment.added "store::write_yaml serializes the Project struct back to YAML, but the Project struct does not model all fields in project.yaml. The release.version-files config is stored as raw YAML but not in the Project struct, so it gets silently dropped on write.\n\nThis affected us when joy auth --token wrote the AI member's public_key -- the entire project.yaml was re-serialized, losing release.version-files.\n\nRoot cause: any command that reads project.yaml into Project struct and writes it back will lose unmodeled fields.\n\nFix options:\n1. Add release config to Project struct (models it properly)\n2. Use YAML-aware merge instead of full re-serialization (preserve unknown keys)\n3. Read-modify-write at YAML level instead of struct level\n\nOption 2 or 3 is more robust. Option 1 is simpler but requires adding every new config key to the struct.\n\nIntegration test needed: write project with extra YAML fields, call a command that modifies project.yaml, verify extra fields survived." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T20:48:29.678Z JOY-008A item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T20:57:12.049Z JOY-008A comment.added "Fixed: session files now per member, not per project.\n\nFilename: sessions/{project_id}--{member}.json (@ replaced with _at_)\nExample: JOY--horst.schwarz_at_joydev.com.json\n\nload_session and remove_session now take member as second parameter.\nAll callers updated: identity.rs, auth.rs, deauth.rs, ai.rs, project.rs.\n\n2 new integration tests:\n- two members can have independent sessions\n- deauth only removes own session" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T20:57:12.064Z JOY-008A item.status_changed "in-progress -> closed" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T20:57:35.506Z JOY-008B item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T21:09:08.307Z JOY-008B comment.added "Fixed with three changes:\n\n1. write_yaml_preserve() in store.rs: preserves top-level YAML keys not modeled in the struct. Uses the struct's values as authoritative, then adds back any unknown keys from the original file. All project.yaml writes now use this function.\n\n2. Session path: ~/.local/state/joy/sessions/ instead of ~/.config/joy/sessions/ (XDG_STATE_HOME compliant -- sessions are runtime state, not user config)\n\n3. Session filename: SHA-256 hash of project_id:member (first 12 bytes, hex) instead of human-readable names. Privacy-safe, deterministic.\n\n3 new integration tests:\n- project.yaml extra fields survive auth init\n- project.yaml extra fields survive member add  \n- project.yaml extra fields survive auth reset\n\n84 total integration tests green." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
