2026-03-28T21:55:18.108Z JOY-008D item.created "Token auth overwrites AI member public_key causing multi-user conflicts" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T21:56:16.855Z JOY-008D comment.added "Bug: joy auth --token writes a derived public_key on the AI member in project.yaml. When a second user authenticates with a different token, the key gets overwritten and the first user's token becomes invalid.\n\nFix: redesign token system with per-delegator token entries.\n\nDesign (documented in Auth.md):\nEach human member gets an ai_tokens map in their project.yaml config:\n\n  bob@team.com:\n    ai_tokens:\n      ai:claude@joy:\n        token_key: <random_pk>   # unique per create-token call\n        created: <timestamp>\n\nToken creation: generates a one-time keypair, stores public key in ai_tokens, signs token with BOTH the human's key (authorization) and the token_key (binding).\n\nToken validation: checks both signatures -- human key (is this person authorized?) AND token_key (does this match a registered token entry?).\n\nRevoke: delete the ai_tokens entry -> token_key gone -> old token invalid. New create-token generates new token_key -> old tokens don't match.\n\nMulti-user safe: each human has their own ai_tokens section, no conflicts.\n\nADR to be written. Auth.md to be updated." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T21:56:16.873Z JOY-008D item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-28T22:09:33.168Z JOY-008D comment.added "Fixed with per-delegator token system (ADR-023):\n\n- Token carries dual Ed25519 signatures: delegator key + one-time token_key\n- Token entries stored per human member in ai_tokens map in project.yaml\n- No public_key written on AI members (no multi-user conflicts)\n- joy ai reset removes ai_tokens entries from all members (global revocation)\n- joy project shows token status for AI members (checks ai_tokens across all members)\n- Session validation for AI: checks local session file only (no project.yaml key needed)\n\nADR-023 written. Auth.md updated. 9 new token unit tests (dual sig, wrong keys, revocation).\n143 unit tests + 86 integration tests green." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
